[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Improving testing conditions**\n\nThe user wants to improve something, but I'm thinking it might be unreachable without some changes. There's local context with an active Java class. Public API use could lead to platform-specific errors. My best option seems to be creating a test for the code path when running on supported Windows. I could use `org.junit.jupiter.api.condition.EnabledOnOs(OS.WINDOWS)`, but I wonder if the coverage run would only work on Windows. It seems OS conditions don't skip the native image, but they won't run on Linux either.\n\n**Analyzing AWT event handling**\n\nI’m thinking about the AWT event dispatch thread and what happens if there’s an invalid class. So, when called on the dispatch thread, `new_Frame` checks if `EventQueue.isDispatchThread` is true and then runs. But if there's a `SWT.error`, it throws from the runnable and propagates out of `new_Frame`. I might be confused because it seems like it only catches `ClassNotFound`, which results in `SWT.error` being thrown. I need to clarify the flow here.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0253e81474ed6bf8016a1e9b0862108194950b07c5724cc78a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqHpsgx7aakxeWxA9lJvzn4APxek80p0mIpwdau-46xrdp9ipPtPckeKrGmedSdxMor8WUxuZQQNYcvwQ7oW5Tmo-vhVcn99d7yYWLIWDo-HmW0qDLt5K7yPsY8-ObUS-xs5vlt_jWudPQQQT85ysO06d5TdzVWZXoxCef0EsLKgV5QX4lot6fD_A75VWrlfrvgHZ9Tet5knIZ4LTnprFxX2aRzH8nmwk6Q4u_NZ0MoWOYNLwvVOR7Ci84AZ_RrEAcw5AvcqzbcJiB0OYqpmG4OE8VMvFi5EfOfG4ewYI7n00d1ZCFHrC7BpeBRz4ttQSz5UieqlDXnIqMhBKBR-JybTwwkSijl2DVIm7R2inpWNNvHikG6TxXaFMU_kimdpxI5qQeq9gL0fNNkaFbXbwZ2tP66il6n7IwexkQ1PUcOSG219aOtlRV-U066Ekd68OgKI4_ZA69mV9GiFfs6PjzSVisAzbUHnXn9Sr1BRScDzf_cIr1zu8UDaNADN6x-z72mgoCx9_BJotsSS4eHSbLmPDmEDy0y7YfraKTuceyo2YWuopm3OH8R62q2CKyqSFh4gUpjbGO5P8jrWBsZLkLqOMb0htVaOrfLAtjOwztm6093AyVocJ4j69Zb2dDxwiBhHDdbSaFEkMPQKpCbS9XZ_tCPaTx3wEpqqfwpIAKRFHHLQ3Lmug6oQH-