not dynamic. I could update the placeholder to public and maybe a no-op, but that may not be necessary. I think about whether all top-level test classes should be public or if we should also change existing ones to public.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_vg5nyg3oNvGYuRltjFf2xpHF|fc_0253e81474ed6bf8016a1e9b5871248194921c8eecce6d5126", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"SWT_AWT\" /home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata-copy/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.swt.win32.win32.x86_64/3.133.0/main -n | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 452, "output": 2019, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38311, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780390713001, "responseId": "resp_0253e81474ed6bf8016a1e9b39c6908194a052d7326cab90cd"}}
